1.name: /advancement
1.value: Gives, removes, or checks player advancements. [See offical documentation.](https://minecraft.gamepedia.com/Commands/advancement)

1.name: /clone <x1> <y1> <z1> <x2> <y2> <z2> <x> <y> <z> [maskMode] [cloneMode] [TileName] [dataValue|state]
1.value: Copies blocks from one place to another.

1.name: /data
1.value: Gets, merges, modifies and removes block entity and entity NBT data. [See official documentation]{https://minecraft.gamepedia.com/Commands/data}

1.name: /debug {start|stop|report}
1.value: Starts or stops a debugging session.

1.name: /deop <player>
1.value: Revokes operator status from a player.

1.name: /fill <x1> <y1> <z1> <x2> <y2> <z2> <block> [destroy|hollow|keep|outline|replace]
1.value: Fills a region with a specific block.

1.name: /forceload add <x1> <z1> [<x2> <z2>]
1.value: Forces a chunk to be constantly loaded.

1.name: /forceload query [<x1> <z1>]
1.value: Tells you if specified chunk is force-loaded.

1.name: /gamerule <rule name> [value]
1.value: Sets or queries a game rule value.

2.name: /give <player> <item>[<NBT>] [<count>]
2.value: Gives an item to a player.

2.name: /kick <player> [reason]
2.value: Kicks a player off a server

2.name: /loot <target> <source>
2.value: Drops itesm from an inventory slot onto the ground.

2.name: /me <action>
2.value: Displays a message about the sender.

2.name: /tell or /msg or /w <player> <message>
2.value: Displays a private message to other players.

2.name: /op <player>
2.value: Grants operator status to a player.

2.name: /publish [port]
2.value: Opens single-player world to local network.

2.name: /reload
2.value: Reloads loot tables, advancements, and functions from disk.

2.name: /say <message>
2.value: Displays a message to multiple players.

2.name: /schedule function <function> <time> [append|replace]
2.value: Delays the execution of a function.

3.name: /setblock
3.value: Changes a block to another block. [See official documentation]{/schedule clear <function>},

3.name: /setidletimeout <minutes until kick>
3.value: Sets the time before idle players are kicked.

3.name: /spawnpoint [<player>] [<x> <y> <z>]
3.value: Sets the spawn point for a player.

3.name: /spectate [target] [player]
3.value: Make one player in spectator mode spectate an entity.

3.name: /teammsg <message>
3.value: Specifies the message to send to the team.

3.name: /tellraw <player> <raw json message>
3.value: Displays a JSON message to players.

3.name: /time <add|query|set> <value>
3.value: Changes or queries the world's game time.

3.name: /trigger <objective> [<add|set> <value>]
3.value: Sets a trigger to be activated.

3.name: /worldborder
3.value: Manages the world border. [See official documentation]{/worldborder},
